CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1962, pg. 11 reads: " Indoor Plants - The breakfast room of the Herbert Simmons' home on Rowan St., is one of the most cheerful rooms in house. Filled with a variety of plants, they bring a touch of spring on the coldest winter day.  Mrs. Simmons demonstrates here, the correct way to transplant a plant to Mrs. Laulie Bolden, left, and Mrs. Eula Reynolds right. - Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Laulie Bolden, Inez Enty Simmons, transplanting a plant, and Eula Reynolds, standing in the Simmons' home
